Class HttpResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.proxysniffer.HttpResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    dfischer.proxysniffer.HttpResponseInterface

    public class HttpResponse
extends java.lang.Object
implements dfischer.proxysniffer.HttpResponseInterface
    Contains all recorded data of a HTTP response.

      • HttpResponse

        public HttpResponse(java.util.Vector<java.lang.String> responseHeaderVector,
            byte[] responseContent,
            long headerReceiveTime,
            long contentWaitTime,
            long contentReceiveTime,
            long responseEndDate)
        Constructs a new instance - used to import HTTP response data from external tools.
        Parameters:
        responseHeaderVector - HTTP response header. The vector must contain at least the first HTTP header field.
        responseContent - HTTP response content, can be null if no response content is available
        headerReceiveTime - time in milliseconds to receive the HTTP response header, can be 0 if no such time is available
        contentWaitTime - time in milliseconds to receive the first byte of HTTP response content, can be 0 if no such time is available
        contentReceiveTime - time in milliseconds to receive all of HTTP response content data, can be 0 if no such time is available
        responseEndDate - end date of the HTTP response, elapsed milliseconds since January 1. 1970, GMT.

      • getCharsetFromResponseContent

        public java.lang.String getCharsetFromResponseContent()
        Try to extract the charset from the HTML or XML response content. The charset can be specified in the response as follows:
        • <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
        • <meta charset="utf-8">
        • <?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1"?>
        Returns:
        the charset from the HTML or XML response content in UPPERCASE, or null if no charset was found
        See Also:
        getContentTypeCharset()

      • getShortLog

        public java.lang.String getShortLog()
        Get a small summary about the HTTP response.
        The information contains:
        • The HTTP status code
        • The HTTP status text (enfolded by double quotes)
        • The content type (or --- if not available)
        • The number of received bytes (or --- if not available)

        Returns:
        a small summary about the HTTP response

        public boolean replaceHeaderField(java.lang.String headerField,
                         java.lang.String fieldValue)
